{%- comment -%} Windows Tile Configuration {%- endcomment -%}
<meta name="msapplication-TileColor" content="#e11d26">
<meta name="msapplication-TileImage" content="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/{{ shop.id | split: '/' | last }}/files/pwa-icon-144.png">
<meta name="msapplication-config" content="none">

{%- comment -%} Prevent auto-detection of phone numbers {%- endcomment -%}
<meta name="format-detection" content="telephone=no">

{%- comment -%}
  Service Worker Registration — DISABLED (H25 fix)

  Shopify serves theme assets (including service-worker.js) from cdn.shopify.com,
  which is a different origin than the shop's domain. The Service Worker spec
  requires that the SW script must be served from the same origin as the page,
  and the SW can only control pages within its scope. Since the asset_url points
  to cdn.shopify.com, the browser will reject the registration with a
  SecurityError because the SW script's origin does not match the page origin.

  Additionally, even if a first-party SW could be registered, Shopify's CDN
  and storefront architecture means the SW cannot control navigation requests
  or cache pages effectively.

  The PWA manifest and meta tags above are kept intact — they still enable
  "Add to Home Screen" functionality and theming on mobile devices.
{%- endcomment -%}
